// ==============================================================================
// ✉️ EMAIL OTP TEST SUITE
// ==============================================================================
//
// NOTE: Replace `PASTE_OTP_FROM_EMAIL`, `PASTE_OLD_OTP`, and `OLD_OTP` 
// with the actual OTP received in your inbox before running the verify/reset tests.
//
// SMTP CONFIGURATION:
// To fully test email delivery locally, you must configure the following in your `.env`:
//   SMTP_USERNAME=your_gmail@gmail.com
//   SMTP_PASSWORD=your_gmail_app_password
//   SMTP_FROM=your_gmail@gmail.com
//
// If these are missing or invalid, the email will fail to send, BUT the API will 
// still return `200 OK`. The OTP will be generated, stored in the DB, and printed 
// to your server terminal (Dev Mode Intercept) so you can still test the flow!
// ==============================================================================

@base_url = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Send OTP — Signup
// Expected: 200 OK, message saying OTP sent
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "purpose": "signup"
}

### 2. Send OTP — Invalid email format
// Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "not-an-email"
}

### 3. Verify OTP — Correct OTP
// Expected: 200 OK, user verified
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "otp": "PASTE_OTP_FROM_EMAIL",
    "purpose": "signup"
}

### 4. Verify OTP — Wrong OTP
// Expected: 400 or 401, OTP invalid error
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "otp": "000000",
    "purpose": "signup"
}

### 5. Verify OTP — Expired OTP (use an old one)
// Expected: 400 or 401, OTP expired error
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "otp": "PASTE_OLD_OTP",
    "purpose": "signup"
}

### 6. Resend OTP
// Expected: 200 OK, new OTP sent (old OTP should be invalidated)
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/resend-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "purpose": "signup"
}

### 7. Verify OLD OTP after resend (should fail)
// Expected: 400 or 401, OTP invalid (already invalidated)
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "otp": "OLD_OTP",
    "purpose": "signup"
}

### 8. Forgot Password — Send OTP
// Expected: 200 OK, OTP sent to email (NO SMS should be triggered)
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/send-forgot-password-link
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com"
}

### 9. Reset Password — Correct OTP
// Expected: 200 OK, password reset successful
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "code": "PASTE_OTP_FROM_EMAIL",
    "new_password": "NewPass@123"
}

### 10. Reset Password — Reuse same OTP (should fail)
// Expected: 400, OTP already used
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@gmail.com",
    "code": "SAME_OTP_AS_ABOVE",
    "new_password": "AnotherPass@123"
}

### 11. Phone OTP still works (regression check)
// Expected: 200 OK, SMS OTP triggered (existing flow not broken)
POST {{base_url}}/api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_no": "+919999999999"
}
